  "body": "**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**\r\n\r\nOn Kiln testnet, CL clients typically connect to JSON-RPC via 8545/8546 for web3,net,eth; and 8551 for engine. Engine API needs to be JWT authenticated. With `--JsonRpc.JwtSecretFile=/var/lib/nethermind/jwtsecret` and `--JsonRpc.AdditionalRpcUrls=http://0.0.0.0:8551|http;wss|engine;eth;net;web3;subscribe`, 8545/8546 end up authenticated as well. This causes issues with CL clients like Lighthouse, and would also cause issues for other RPC consumers like my chainlink nodes.\r\n\r\n**Describe the solution you'd like**\r\n\r\nBe able to specify authentication by API. Ideally I can force authentication for `engine` while leaving all other methods unauthenticated.\r\n\r\nThis is currently the behavior of Geth, Besu and Erigon.\r\n",
